@flexiarg war-room/wr-3-social-exotype-before-implementation
@title WR-3: Social Exotype Before Implementation
@sigils [⚖/令]
@audience futon stack operators, agents, mission authors
@tone foundational
@style pattern

! conclusion: Write and validate the social exotype diagram before writing any social-layer implementation code.

  + context: War Room decision WR-3 (2026-02-09). Operator: Joe.

  + IF:
    futon3c needs to implement Agency, Forum, peripherals, and bridges.

  + HOWEVER:
    Three previous attempts at social-layer code failed, Agency across three generations, Forum abandoned, the bridge in a perpetual fix-cycle, because invariants were discovered retroactively instead of specified proactively.

  + THEN:
    Write the social exotype diagram and validate it before writing any futon3c implementation code. Extend the futon5 composition framework to validate the three-diagram stack, futon3a and futon3b and futon3c, as one system.

  + BECAUSE:
    The derivation xenotype requires VERIFY before INSTANTIATE. The coordination rewrite succeeded because the exotype existed before the gates, and the social loop must follow the same path. The composition framework is isomorphic to pheno-geno-exo stacking in futon5, so building it earns the theoretical readiness, mana, that unblocks gated futon5 missions.

    + evidence: The social ARGUMENT flexiarg establishes the S, R, and C clauses. futon3b succeeded with an exotype-first approach, eight of eight checks and thirty-one tests. futon5 missions gated on mana are gated on composition validation capability.
